# EDAMAME CLI - RPC Interface

## Documentation (Read First)
Before making changes, consult these files:
- **CLAUDE.md** - Build commands, CLI commands
- **ARCHITECTURE.md** - Single-file architecture, RPC dispatch
- **README.md** - Installation and usage guide

## Project Context
EDAMAME CLI provides direct RPC access to edamame_core:
- Method discovery (`list-methods`, `get-method-info`)
- RPC execution (`rpc <method> [json_args]`)
- Interactive REPL mode
- Shell completions

## Key Files
- `src/main.rs` - Single-file implementation (~700 lines)
  - `build_cli()` - CLI construction
  - `handle_rpc()` - RPC call handler
  - `interactive_mode()` - REPL implementation

## Build & Test
```bash
cargo build --release
make test
```

## Usage Examples
```bash
edamame-cli list-methods
edamame-cli rpc get_score --pretty
edamame-cli rpc method_name '["arg1", 42]'
edamame-cli interactive
```

## Part of EDAMAME Ecosystem
Uses `edamame_core` with `swiftrs` feature. See `../edamame_core/CLAUDE.md` for the full ecosystem.
